I've been thinking about this, and I think we can implement a better solution. `uuid` field has several advantages like optimization, better indexing, etc... so we should try to keep it.

So we could use a deterministic function that converts firebaseID to uuids (on the import script). Something like:

```ts
import { v5 as uuidv5 } from "uuid";

 // RANDOM UUID to server as a base. It's safe for this to be public
const FIREBASE_TO_UUID_NAMESPACE = "ddeb27fb-d9a0-4624-be4d-4615062daed4";

// This will always return the same uuid with a given firebase ID
export function convertFirebaseIdToUuid(firebaseId: string) {
  return uuidv5(firebaseId, NAMESPACE);
}
```

If we do redirections on BG3.5, we can always compute this an redirect to the right uuid.

